# infra/compose/caddy/Caddyfile
#
# Same-origin routing per docs/architecture/overview.md's Container
# diagram: web at `/`, API reverse-proxied at `/api/*`. No web/api
# container exists yet (slices 6/8) — the reverse_proxy directives
# below are commented out so this slice proves only "config parses,
# container runs, a stub responds." Uncommenting is an additive edit
# for slices 6/8, not a Caddyfile rewrite.
#
# The site address comes from $SITE_ADDRESS so one file serves both
# overlays (ADR 0004's "same service defs, overlay flips
# tags/limits/volumes" pattern): compose.yml defaults it to `:80`
# (plain HTTP, no TLS); compose.prod.yml sets it to a real domain,
# which switches Caddy's automatic HTTPS/ACME on.

{$SITE_ADDRESS:80} {
	# reverse_proxy /api/* api:8080
	# reverse_proxy web:3000

	respond "ok" 200
}
